1309":"1309","1290":"1290","Utterby, Lincolnshire, England":"Utterby, Lincolnshire, England","Burgh on Bain, Lincolnshire, England":"Burgh on Bain, Lincolnshire, England"},"en":{"1282–1310":"1282–1310","1278–1309":"1278–1309","1310–1387":"1310–1387","1302":"1302","1278":"1278","1310":"1310","1387":"1387","1282":"1282","1309":"1309","1290":"1290","Utterby, Lincolnshire, England":"Utterby, Lincolnshire, England","Burgh on Bain, Lincolnshire, England":"Burgh on Bain, Lincolnshire, England","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Girsby","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English: possibly a habitational name from a lost orunidentified place."],"variants":[]},{"name":"Joan","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Contracted form of Old French <i>Jo(h)anne</i>, from Latin <i>Io(h)anna</i> (  see  Joanna  ). In England this was the usual feminine form of   John   from the Middle English period onwards and was extremely popular, but in the 16th and 17th centuries it steadily lost ground to   Jane .  It was strongly revived in the first part of the 20th century, partly under the influence of  George Bernard Shaw's  play St Joan (  1923 ), based on the life of  Joan of Arc  (  1412–31 ). Claiming to be guided by the voices of the saints, she persuaded the French dauphin to defy the occupying English forces and have himself crowned, and she led the French army that raised the siege of Orleans in  1429 . The following year she was captured by the Burgundians and sold to the English, and a year later she was burned at the stake for witchcraft at the age of 18 or 19. Her story has captured the imagination of many writers, and she is variously portrayed as a national and political hero, a model of apolitical straightforwardness and honesty, and a religious heroine. She was canonized in  1920 . More recent influences have included the American film actress  Joan Crawford  (  1908–77 , born  Lucille le Sueur ), the British actress  Joan Collins  (  b. 1933 ), the American comedienne  Joan Rivers  (  b. 1933 ), and the West Indian pop singer  Joan Armatrading  (  b. 1950 )."],"variants":[{"name":"John","meanings":["Greek: the Lord gave graciously; whom Jehovah gave; whom Jehovah bestowed."]}]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705190,"age":8,"year":"1290","julianDay":2192224,"title":"Jews Expelled From England","description":"After years of anti-Semitic behavior, King Edward I expelled Jews from England in 1290.","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"Joan Girsby was born in 1282, in Burgh on Bain, Lincolnshire, England. She married Robert Hawley in 1302, in Burgh on Bain, Lincolnshire, England. They were the parents of at least 1 son. She died in 1310, in Utterby, Lincolnshire, England, at the age of 28."},"et":{"1282–1310":"1282–1310","1278–1309":"1278–1309","1310–1387":"1310–1387","1302":"1302","1278":"1278","1310":"1310","1387":"1387","1282":"1282","1309":"1309","1290":"1290","Utterby, Lincolnshire, England":"Utterby, Lincolnshire, England","Burgh on Bain, Lincolnshire, England":"Burgh on Bain, Lincolnshire, England"},"fi":{"1282–1310":"1282–1310","1278–1309":"1278–1309","1310–1387":"1310–1387","1302":"1302","1278":"1278","1310":"1310","1387":"1387","1282":"1282","1309":"1309","1290":"1290","Utterby, Lincolnshire, England":"Utterby, Lincolnshire, England","Burgh on Bain, Lincolnshire, England":"Burgh on Bain, Lincolnshire, England"},"fr":{"1282–1310":"1282–1310","1278–1309":"1278–1309","1310–1387":"1310–1387","1302":"1302","1278":"1278","1310":"1310","1387":"1387","1282":"1282","1309":"1309","1290":"1290","Utterby, Lincolnshire, England":"Utterby, Lincolnshire, Angleterre","Burgh on Bain, Lincolnshire, England":"Burgh on Bain, Lincolnshire, Angleterre","lifeSummary":"Joan Girsby est née en 1282, à Burgh on Bain, Lincolnshire, Angleterre. Elle a épousé Robert Hawley en 1302, à Burgh on Bain, Lincolnshire, Anglet